This paper deals with security and privacy issues in computer systems, specifically in the context of Intel SGX. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves software engineering aspects, such as the development of malware and the use of Docker containers, which makes cs.SE (Software Engineering) a likely category as well. The paper also involves hardware aspects, such as the use of cache side-channel attacks, which makes cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible category. Additionally, the paper involves aspects of computer architecture and design, which makes cs.AR (Architecture) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves programming language aspects, such as the use of constant-time multiplication primitives, which makes cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible category.
